{
    "name": "Mage for Hire",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Mage for Hire",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "Not all mercenaries sell brawn and intimidating glares. Some sell their magical talents to earn a living. While there are many types of mages for hire, some of the sneakiest are specialized in divination, using their skills for infiltration and sabotage.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 22
                    },
                    "page": 226
                }
            ],
            "links": [
                {
                    "type": "link",
                    "name": "divination",
                    "alt": "divination",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 47
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Mercenaries",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Bribing Mercenaries",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Unless a mercenary prides themself on their name or reputation, the PCs might be able to bribe them to switch sides, or at least stand aside. You can estimate a bribe by taking roughly 5% of the Party Currency value from the row corresponding to the NPC's level on Table 10\u20139.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 22
                            },
                            "page": 226
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "links": [
                        {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Table 10\u20139",
                            "alt": "Table 10\u20139",
                            "game-obj": "Rules",
                            "aonid": 581
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Mercenary Banter",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Here's some parlance commonly used by mercenaries.   \n  \n**Crackster**: Someone adept at breaking locks or safes.   \n**Diving**: Theft or smuggling below ground, often through tunnels.   \n**Foxing**: To play at being asleep, usually for an ambush.   \n**Medic**: A healer.   \n**Ram**: A hard-hitting warrior.   \n**Slinger**: A spellcaster.   \n**Sway of Coin**: Swearing allegiance to whoever pays the most.   \n**Waterline**: A mercenary troupe's money: \u201cTake time in town while the waterline's high, everyone.\u201d   \n**Whisperstep**: Anyone who can move stealthily.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 22
                            },
                            "page": 226
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "A broad category that includes those wielding arms, spells, or even guile and cunning, mercenaries hire themselves and their expertise to those with the gold to pay for it.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 226",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 22
                    },
                    "page": 226
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
